<font color="#FF0000">THE &quot;IT&quot; THAT WILL NOT DIE</font><br>
<tt>Mon Oct 27 20:28:56 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
MTF and John,<br><br>
I have suggested that we ignore these things.  I have been trying and am still struggling with that effort.  Some things or people do not fade away or just shut up.  A lot likes a child who must have the final word.  If we treat such like the infantile behavior it exhibits then we walk away and never give it a chance to close.  Just ignore it.  I choose the word &quot;IT&quot; because I am not going to give &quot;IT&quot; a human side.  &quot;IT&quot; is a thing.  A thing that manifests itself in the human who is in an agonizing struggle with its sanity.<br><br>
If we kill &quot;IT then what do we do with &quot;IT&quot;.  Skin it, bury it, or just kick it around for the hell of it.  A circle that does little for us.  The guys that are here needed this release.  A lot of anger has been held back.  Statements from &quot;IT&quot; burn deep.  Vicious things that can't be forgiven.<br><br>
I will continue to not respond to &quot;IT because I have better things to do with my BOC.  We can and have risen above things worse than this.<br><br>
I suggest Ed we either take the scalp or leave &quot;IT&quot; to the buzzards.  The hunt is over and the beast will not die.  I am sure that some where in your native lore there is a saying that will give us closure that will allow us to move on.<br><br>
Your Brother of Choice<br><br>
SW<br>

